@node "Document_16" "THE STORM"

   @{b}THE STORM@{ub}

   @{i}by Mauricio Santinelli@{ui}


   I'm sitting in the  devil's  chair.   Down below you can see
   any variety of seashells and a large snail stands out.  I am
   impatiently waiting for the stars to show  up  on  the  sea.
   Last  night  they  were out very early.  Charles is fishing.
   Well, that's what he  says,  I've  only  seen him launch his
   bait and not catch anything.  But Charles doesn't care about
   that, he doesn't care because that is the way he has fun.

   We have been here for two days and one night there and  have
   not gotten bored.  We are waiting for the equinox storm.  We
   have  come  here  together  for the last ten years.  We have
   always arrived two before September 22nd.  The storm started
   on the 22nd with the equinox  and ended on the 25th with the
   full moon.

   One day I tried to convince him that we should  get  out  of
   the  sea  while  the  storm was raging, the wind was blowing
   very strong and the rain beat  on our bodies, the waves were
   huge, they were over 9 feet high.  Let's get away from  here
   !,  I yelled.  Idon't know if the raging waves did not allow
   him to her me of if he did not wan to hear me.

   When we go out, Charles looked at me without blinking.

   - What were you saying in the sea ?  he asked.  - I said  we
   should  get out...  -Why ?  he asked again.  - I was afraid,
   the storm had never been  this furious.  Besides that, I was
   cold, I answered sincerely.  - I can believe you were  cold,
   he  said,  but  cannot  believe  you were afraid.  - You can
   think whatever you want, you are completely crazy.  - So are
   you.  Otherwise you would  not  be  here.   You would not be
   here.  You would rather die than not be  somebody  in  life.
   If  I  am going to die, I want to die here, in the waves, in
   the sea and I know you feel the same way.

   He said no more.  We kept  walking with our boards under our
   arms until we reached the car.

   Charles quit fishing and went to sit down, he too is waiting
   for the stars.  The stars shows us the storm's intensity.

   - There are no starts,  I said.
   - This will be a violent year, he responded after a while.

   The next day we were our on  the  beach  quite  early.   The
   morning  was  cloudy  and rainy.  And the waves beat against
   each other.  We  had  everything  prepared,  the boards were
   waxed and the  locks  were  in  their  place,  brushing  our
   ankles.

   - Are you ready ? he asked.

   I shook my head affirming I was ready.

   - Good.  Here we go -he said.

   We  ran  out  towards  the  sea.  The water was cold but our
   suits would keep our  temperature  so  we would not feel the
   cold.  Almost without realizing  it,  we  were  surfing  the
   waves.

   It's  a  felling that can't be described..  It's almost like
   being suspended in the space.   It's  like being owner of an
   infinite for a time, and tinne is decided by us.  It's  like
   controlling a chimera which is out off itself.

   Charles  was  at  the  left,  a  little beat forward me.  An
   immense wave loomed in the  distance.  Charles made me signs
   so that we went to that direction.  We were going  to  enter
   into  room  "B".  I don't know if it was us who came into it
   or it was the wave.   In  those very moment you never think,
   you just let your self be free.  Inside room "B"  everything
   is  calm.   This  green turquoise color from the walls makes
   you feel an inner  peace  that  you  hardly get in any other
   exterior place.  When you came into it  you  don't  want  to
   leave,  buty  it  is  not  in  our  hands  but in those from
   nature's.  We came out of it.   We were tired but joyful.  I
   shouted to Charles and we bearded to the shore.  We have  to
   keep  some energy for the afternoon it is then when appear a
   real storm.

   We leant on the sand for a while.  Then we rinsed the boards
   with clean water and we polished  them with wax so that they
   were ready for that afternoon.  While we were polishing  the
   boards we were very quiet.  I know Charles since we were 10,
   so I knew something was wrong with him.

   - Are you afraid ? - I asked.
   -  I  have a presentiment...- he answered without looking at
   me.  - Nothing  wrong  is  going  to  happen.  Waves are our
   friends, we'll be safe.

   Charles agreed smiling.

   The sky was completely dark.  The rain  spattered  intensely
   on the sea.  The daylight was not as clear as before.

   There  were  only  medium waves.  We slid without difficulty
   moving with rhythm from  one  side  to the other and beating
   the boards against the water.  To get more speed.   We  were
   specting  the  huge  monster,  That's  have  we call the big
   waves.  We wanted to  fight  it.  The Monster is omnipotent,
   but it still has a weak point, just as humans.  There  is  a
   fantasy  in  his mind, ans illusion, it could have the shape
   and size that we  want  it  to  have,  and  it makes it more
   dangerous.  The big monster appered in the distance,  so  we
   went  towards it.  Charles turn to look at me.  The more the
   wave was near us, I could  realize  the size it had.  It was
   the biggest monster I had never seen.  It keep straighten up
   with its huge fauces.

   Charles shouted at me over  the  waves,  we  were  going  to
   enter.  I was scared.

   Before  to  enter, I realized that monster haven came alone,
   the daughter's wave  to  deflected  me strongly.  I couldn't
   keep the balance.  Before to felt down I turn to look to  my
   friend.   The  last  thing  that  I saw was Charles to going
   toward the monster.  The big  wave crashed with me.  It's to
   sinked me and remained me  into  its  profundity  without  I
   couldn't  do  anythting,  swallowed  salty water, and I felt
   that  I  wouldn't  go   out   of   sea.   I  remembered  the
   presentiment.  Suddenly I saw the surface,  there  were  not
   vestiges  of  monster  and Charles neither ...  Desperatly I
   reached him without found  him.   After  a time there wasn't
   any posibility.  I continue  going  to  the  equinox  storm.
   Before to enter, I look the sky reaching my friend.  Charles
   knew  it and was his wish.  Now I Know too, If I am going to
   die, I want to  die  in  the  waves.   I isn't afraid to the
   monster, because somebody care me there in the sky.
